<HEADLINE> EC Denies Plans to Delay Launch of Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 29 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
spokesman today formally denied newspaper reports that the EC is
"secretly" drawing up plans to delay the launch of the single
currency, the Euro.
</P>
<P>
"The commission firmly sticks to its position that the Euro
shall be introduced in conformity with the (Maastricht) Treaty
criteria and timetable which have been confirmed by the December
European Council of Madrid," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
At the Madrid summit last December, leaders of EU member
nations agreed unanimously that the European single currency will
be formally launched on January 1, 1999. 
</P>
